=={{en}}==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[concordans]]'', present participle of ''[[concordare]]'': compare French concordant.  See [[concord]] 
===Adjective===
#[[Agree]]ing; [[correspondent]]; [[harmonious]]; [[consonant]]; [[in keeping]] with; [[agreeable]] with; [[concordant]] with; [[concordant]] to
#*Were every one employed in points [[concordant]] to their natures, professions, and arts, commonwealths would rise up of themselves. - Sir [[Thomas Browne]]

